Below is one systematic way to “decode” and rebuild the scene exactly as shown, using only the orientations given in the dictionary images (no re‐orientations).  I have broken the explanation into three parts:

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)  DETAILED DESCRIPTION OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
•  Overall there are two separate structures:

  A)  The “Truck” (left side in the image)
     –  Layers & Block Count:
        1.  A single yellow rectangular prism as the main chassis (appears as one thick yellow layer).  
        2.  On top at the rear is a green rectangular block.  
        3.  On top at the front are two cubes side‐by‐side (one blue and one red), capped by a yellow half‐cylinder “roof.”  
        4.  Two orange cylinders (lying horizontally) serve as wheels.
     –  Thus the truck uses 7 pieces total:
        •  1 × yellow rectangular block (chassis)  
        •  1 × green rectangular block (rear bed)  
        •  1 × blue cube  
        •  1 × red cube  
        •  1 × yellow half‐cylinder (roof)  
        •  2 × orange horizontal cylinders (wheels)

  B)  The “Arch‐Tower” (right side in the image)
     –  Layers & Block Count (bottom to top):
        1.  Bottom layer of three red arch‐blocks side by side (forming three arches across the front).  
        2.  One flat yellow rectangular block spanning the entire second layer.  
        3.  A red “circular window” section made from two matching red half‐circle blocks (stacked vertically) so as to form a complete large circular hole through the middle.  
        4.  A second flat yellow rectangular block capping the top.  
     –  Hence the tower uses 7 pieces total:
        •  3 × red arch blocks (for the base arches)  
        •  1 × yellow rectangular block (mid‐level)  
        •  2 × red “C‐shape” pieces (stacked to form the circular window)  
        •  1 × yellow rectangular block (top level)

•  Total Blocks Used in the Scene = 7 (truck) + 7 (tower) = 14.  
•  Number of Layers:  
  –  The truck effectively has 2 main layers (chassis layer + top cubes/roof), with wheels attached at the base.  
  –  The tower has 4 “layers” (arch base → yellow slab → circular window → yellow top).  

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2)  MATCHING EACH PART TO THE DICTIONARY BLOCKS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Below is one possible exact match from the dictionary without rotating any piece:

●  TRUCK
   1)  Yellow chassis   → use block #10 (a flat yellow rectangular prism oriented long‐ways).  
   2)  Green rear block  → use block #8 (short green rectangular prism).  
   3)  Blue cube         → block #5.  
   4)  Red cube          → block #7.  
   5)  Yellow half‐cyl.  → block #15 (the half‐cylinder in yellow, lying “east‐west”).  
   6)  Orange wheels     → block #14 (the orange cylinder lying horizontally).  We need two of these, so #14 is used twice.

●  ARCH‐TOWER
   1)  Red base arches   → block #1 three times (all oriented as arches front‐to‐back).  
   2)  Yellow mid‐slab   → block #11 (a slightly longer yellow rectangular prism, also oriented lengthwise).  
   3)  Red circular hole → block #4 twice (two matching “C‐shapes,” stacked to form the large round opening).  
   4)  Yellow top slab   → block #12 (another yellow rectangular prism, also lengthwise).

Hence the indices needed are:

- (Truck)  #10, #8, #5, #7, #15, #14×2  
- (Tower)  #1×3, #11, #4×2, #12  

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Below is one logical sequence (you can assemble tower first or truck first—any order works).  Here is an example tower‐then‐truck order:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 1      // 1st red arch (tower base)
  Step2:  Move block with index 1      // 2nd red arch (tower base)
  Step3:  Move block with index 1      // 3rd red arch (tower base)
  Step4:  Move block with index 11     // yellow rectangle above arches
  Step5:  Move block with index 4      // bottom half of the circular window
  Step6:  Move block with index 4      // top half of the circular window
  Step7:  Move block with index 12     // yellow rectangle on top

  Step8:  Move block with index 10     // truck’s yellow chassis
  Step9:  Move block with index 8      // green rectangular block (rear of truck)
  Step10: Move block with index 5      // blue cube (truck front)
  Step11: Move block with index 7      // red cube (truck front)
  Step12: Move block with index 15     // yellow half-cylinder (truck roof)
  Step13: Move block with index 14     // first orange cylinder (wheel)
  Step14: Move block with index 14     // second orange cylinder (wheel)
}

That completes the build exactly as shown in the reference image, using only the unrotated blocks from the dictionary.
